<span id="ii.xx-p102"></span> Codd. Monac. Vind. Roe. Casaub. add <span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xx-p102.1"></span>καὶ τί πιστεύομεν</span>.

<span id="fn_2043"></span>[121:2044](2070032.htm#fr_2043.md) <span
id="ii.xx-p102.2"></span>

<span id="ii.xx-p103"></span> The terms <span class="Greek"><span
id="ii.xx-p103.1"></span>παροικία</span>, the See of a Bishop, and <span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xx-p103.2"></span>ἐ</span><span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xx-p103.3"></span>παρχία</span>, the Province
of a Metropolitan, were both adopted from the corresponding divisions of
the Roman Empire.  See Bingham, *Antt*. Book IX. i. §§ 2–6.

<span id="fn_2044"></span>[121:2045](2070032.htm#fr_2044.md) <span
id="ii.xx-p104.1"></span>

<span id="ii.xx-p105"></span> S. Basil (*De Spiritu S.* c. xvi. § 38),
after quoting the same passage, [Col. i.
16](../../../bib/kjv/col001.htm#016.md)<span id="ii.xx-p105.1"></span>,
proceeds—<span class="Greek"><span id="ii.xx-p105.2"></span>εἴτε
κυριότητες, καὶ εἴ τινές εἰσιν ἕτεραι λογικαὶ φύσεις
ἁκατονόμαστοι</span>.  The last word shews that Basil had in mind this
passage of Cyril, who after the names of nations in § 22, adds <span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xx-p105.3"></span>καὶ τοὺς λοίπους
ἀκατονομάστους ἡμῖν</span>.

